{
  "id": "S2PTF040",
  "title": {
    "product_var": "ZPRODTSK",
    "text": "TERMINAL FUNCTION - [CURSOR-SELECT]",
    "version_var": "ZSHRTVER",
    "prefix": "HELP"
  },
  "type": "menu",
  "body": {
    "rows": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "variable": "ZCMD"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Purpose"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Perform a \"Select\" function on the object the cursor is currently"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "pointing at.  Performs Enter key processing."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Format"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "[CURSOR-SELECT]"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Remarks"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "A \"Select\" is an overloaded function which performs differently"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "in different parts of SPF/PC.  When a [CURSOR-SELECT] key is"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "pressed from a Dialog Manager menu, the menu option that the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "cursor is on top of is selected, if pressed in a selection"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "list, then an 'S' verb is applied to the table row, and if"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "pressed within the editor, then Enter key processing occurs."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "This function is patterned after the [CURSOR-MOUSE-SELECT]"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "function, which enables you to Select different functions by"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "double-clicking on them.  When assigned to a key, it is useful"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "for creating point-and-shoot keys that can select options all"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "over SPF/PC."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "field_row",
        "fields": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "(Press"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "ENTER+to return to menu)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
